# WHAT IT IS
#   Bayard is the **distributed Rust-native search server** тАФ
#   structurally positioned as:
#
#     тАв **Elasticsearch alternative** тАФ without the JVM, without
#       the licensing change to SSPL, written from scratch in
#       Rust with a memory footprint typically 10├Ч smaller per
#       node
#     тАв **OpenSearch alternative** тАФ but tantivy-native instead
#       of Lucene-via-JNI
#     тАв **Meilisearch alternative** тАФ but distributed (Bayard is
#       Raft-replicated multi-node;  Meilisearch is single-node)
#     тАв **Toshi alternative** тАФ toshi-search/Toshi is the
#       similar-shape predecessor (also tantivy-based, also
#       Raft-replicated);  Bayard adds the SWIM gossip layer +
#       multi-language CJK tokenization
#     тАв **Quickwit alternative** тАФ Quickwit is the same-shape
#       cloud-native sibling (also tantivy-based) but
#       optimized for cold-storage S3 / GCS / object-store
#       indices + decoupled compute;  Bayard is cluster-with-
#       local-storage
#
#   Bayard operates as a single binary that joins a cluster via
#   `--seed-address`, advertises itself via SWIM gossip, and
#   serves both gRPC (the internal cluster + client communications
#   API) and HTTP (the public REST API) endpoints.
#
#   Command-line surface (single-mode server;  all configuration
#   via flags, no subcommands):
#
#     тАв -b, --bind-address <addr>     internal cluster
#                                     communications bind address
#                                     (default `0.0.0.0:2000`)
#     тАв -a, --advertise-address <addr>
#                                     advertise address (the
#                                     address gossiped to other
#                                     cluster nodes;  defaults to
#                                     --bind-address)
#     тАв -s, --seed-address <addr>     seed address (the
#                                     bootstrap-peer address used
#                                     when joining an existing
#                                     cluster)
#     тАв -g, --grpc-address <addr>     gRPC bind address (internal
#                                     cluster + client RPC;
#                                     default `0.0.0.0:5000`)
#     тАв -H, --http-address <addr>     HTTP bind address (public
#                                     REST API;  default
#                                     `0.0.0.0:8000`)
#     тАв -d, --data-directory <path>   node data directory (stores
#                                     cluster state, index data,
#                                     metastore;  default
#                                     `/tmp/bayard`)
#     тАв -h, --help                    Show help
#     тАв -V, --version                 Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `mosuka/bayard`'s `bayard/Cargo.toml` declares a **direct**
#   dependency on `tantivy = "0.18.0"` (alongside
#   `lindera-tantivy = "0.16.2"` for CJK morphological tokenization
#   тАФ itself a thin adapter that exposes the typed
#   `lindera::tokenizer::Tokenizer` as a typed
#   `tantivy::tokenizer::Tokenizer` impl).  The
#   `bayard::index::indexer` module uses typed `tantivy::Index` /
#   `tantivy::schema::SchemaBuilder` / `tantivy::IndexWriter` /
#   `tantivy::query::QueryParser` / `tantivy::collector::TopDocs` /
#   `tantivy::DocAddress` primitives;  the typed
#   `tantivy::tokenizer::TokenizerManager` is populated with the
#   lindera tokenizer at startup per the typed
#   `lindera_tantivy::tokenizer::LinderaTokenizer::from_config`
#   constructor.
#
#   **tantivy** (`tantivy` crate) is **THE canonical pure-Rust
#   full-text search engine library** тАФ Paul Masurel's reference
#   pure-safe-Rust implementation of an inverted-index search
#   engine modeled architecturally on Apache Lucene (the JVM
#   library that powers Elasticsearch, Solr, OpenSearch, and
#   essentially every full-text-search system since 2000).  In
#   active development since 2016, with 14,000+ тШЕ on
#   github.com/quickwit-oss/tantivy.  The project is sponsored
#   primarily by Quickwit Inc. (Paul Masurel co-founded
#   Quickwit, the cloud-native search startup built on top of
#   tantivy) and the Quickwit Foundation;  the GitHub org
#   reflects this (`quickwit-oss/tantivy` rather than
#   `tantivy-rs/tantivy`).
#
#   tantivy ships:
#
#     тАв Typed `Index`                  the top-level inverted-
#                                      index handle, with typed
#                                      `Index::builder()` /
#                                      `Index::create_in_dir()` /
#                                      `Index::open_in_dir()` /
#                                      `Index::create_in_ram()`
#                                      constructors
#     тАв Typed `IndexWriter`            with typed
#                                      `IndexWriter::add_document`,
#                                      `IndexWriter::delete_term`,
#                                      `IndexWriter::commit`,
#                                      `IndexWriter::rollback`,
#                                      `IndexWriter::merge`,
#                                      `IndexWriter::garbage_collect_files`
#                                      operations
#     тАв Typed `IndexReader`            with typed
#                                      `IndexReader::reload` for
#                                      Near-Real-Time (NRT)
#                                      search semantics
#     тАв Typed `Searcher`               with typed
#                                      `Searcher::search`,
#                                      `Searcher::search_with_executor`,
#                                      `Searcher::doc`,
#                                      `Searcher::space_usage`
#                                      operations
#     тАв Typed `schema::Schema` +
#       `SchemaBuilder`                with typed field-type
#                                      builders: typed
#                                      `TextOptions` (typed
#                                      indexing, typed
#                                      `IndexRecordOption`,
#                                      typed tokenizer name),
#                                      typed `NumericOptions`
#                                      (typed indexing,
#                                      `STORED`, `FAST`), typed
#                                      `BytesOptions`, typed
#                                      `IpAddrOptions`, typed
#                                      `JsonObjectOptions`,
#                                      typed `FacetOptions`,
#                                      typed `DateOptions`,
#                                      typed `BoolOptions`
#     тАв Typed field-value primitives   typed
#                                      `schema::Value`,
#                                      `schema::Field`,
#                                      `schema::FieldType`,
#                                      `schema::Document`,
#                                      `schema::OwnedValue`,
#                                      `schema::Term`,
#                                      `schema::FieldEntry`,
#                                      `schema::IndexRecordOption`
#                                      (the inverted-index
#                                      record-level options:
#                                      typed `Basic` / `WithFreqs`
#                                      / `WithFreqsAndPositions`)
#     тАв Typed query AST                typed `query::Query`
#                                      trait + concrete typed
#                                      `query::TermQuery`,
#                                      `query::TermSetQuery`,
#                                      `query::PhraseQuery`,
#                                      `query::PhrasePrefixQuery`,
#                                      `query::FuzzyTermQuery`,
#                                      `query::BooleanQuery`,
#                                      `query::RangeQuery`,
